President Trump has declared a state of emergency in Mississippi following the effects of Hurricane Nate. This declaration allows the Department of Homeland Security's Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate relief efforts and provide assistance to the affected areas. FEMA is authorized to mobilize equipment and resources to alleviate the impacts of the emergency, with 75 percent of funding coming from the federal government. Manny J. Toro has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.